cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the environmental impact of training neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact on the energy grid and hardware, which could fall under cs.CE (Computers and Society) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses concrete actions that can be taken to mitigate carbon emissions, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
